#â”‹      did: - (NOTE: the positioning of these comments were illegal, please move them to the end of the file to reduce clutter before the next push!)                                                      â”‹
#â”‹           - MOVED: to 37                                                                                                                                                                                 â”‹
#â”‹           - Quick backreference on lstat/stat indicies refs                                                                                                                                              â”‹
#â”‹              0 dev      device number of filesystem                                                                                                                                                      â”‹
#â”‹              1 ino      inode number                                                                                                                                                                     â”‹
#â”‹              2 mode     File Permissions (Octets: Special, GroupOwnerPerms, UserOwnerPerms, EveryonePerms*)                                                                                              â”‹
#â”‹              3 nlink    File's Hardlink Count (this should NEVER be zero)                                                                                                                                â”‹
#â”‹              4 uid      Owning UID (User ID Number, root is 0)                                                                                                                                           â”‹
#â”‹              5 gid      Owning GID (Group ID Number, root is 0)                                                                                                                                          â”‹
#â”‹              6 rdev     for special files, provides a device ID                                                                                                                                          â”‹
#â”‹              7 size     file's size, in bytes (8 bits = 1 byte)                                                                                                                                          â”‹
#â”‹              8 atime    last access time          ( these are measured in: [seconds - epoch],                                                                                                            â”‹
#â”‹              9 mtime    last modify time            on modern systems, this is Jan 1, 1970, it                                                                                                           â”‹
#â”‹             10 ctime    inode change time           varies greatly on antiquated systems)                                                                                                                â”‹
#â”‹             11 blksize  I/O block size preferred when transferring data to/from file (can vary)                                                                                                          â”‹
#â”‹             12 blocks   "system specific" blocks on the disk (one block is usually 512 bytes)                                                                                                            â”‹
#â”‹             Permissions: 1 = Read 2 = Write 4 = Execute (example Read+Execute for all users would be 0555)                                                                                               â”‹
